<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="381" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1086,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Holotype</typeStatus>
description
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,674,1122,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Structural features of head and thorax much as described above for 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,259,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,259,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">A. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[266,355,1158,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,355,1158,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except median length of crown approximately 9/10 interocular width and 1/2 transocular width, pronotum with posterior margin strongly concave, and forewings translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1086,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1230,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Color.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[496,583,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black with many irregular yellow spots, except disc of pronotum with green spots; apex of scutellum greenish-white. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[998,1136,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Figs. 26–27</figureCitation>
) translucent, except small yellow markings and brown area at base; veins brown. Face (
<figureCitation box="[849,932,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black; frons with three large yellow areas, two inferior and one superior. Lateral and ventral portions of thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1188,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black with yellow markings; legs (
<figureCitation box="[470,552,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) mostly yellow with brown portions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="381" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1086,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1410,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[485,568,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly, expanded apically. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[223,308,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subtriangular; base with lateral projection directed anteriorly (central emarginate area between pair of projections covered by valve); basal portion slightly expanded laterally, then tapering gradually towards apex; latter slightly curved dorsally; without “articulated” portion; in lateral view, plate extending almost as far posteriorly as pygofer apex. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[895,980,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped; stalk narrow and very elongate, with dorsal median keel; arms poorly developed. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1118,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extremely elongate, extending posteriorly much farther than apex of connective, almost as far posteriorly as apex of subgenital plate; without preapical or median lobe; apex acute. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1092,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, curved dorsally on apical half, with large, dorsoapical rectangular lobe and pair of elongate, slightly asymmetrical apical processes that are not located at same plane. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1090,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) without processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1086,1939]" box="[199,400,1770,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="381" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1086,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1806,1831]" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[694,791,1806,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="381" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distincta">
<emphasis box="[694,791,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">distincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to the conspicuous features of the aedeagus, 
<emphasis box="[1395,1429,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">i.e.</emphasis>
, lobe and processes (
<figureCitation box="[376,460,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1476,1499]" captionTargetBox="[179,1394,218,1430]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,195,1455]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. Acrogonia distincta sp. nov. 26, body, male holotype (DZUP), dorsolateral view (total length 9.8 mm); 27, body, male holotype, lateral view; 28–32, male genitalia: 28, pygofer, lateral view; 29, subgenital plates, ventral view (valve not depicted); 30, styles and connective, dorsal view; 31, aedeagus, lateral view; 32, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 28–30, 32 = 1 mm; 31 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155377/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="381">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
